{"questionId":"15303600","questionHtml":"<p>At point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math>,&nbsp;show that the curves&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;intersect at right-angles.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">attempts implicit differentiation on either curve&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent) and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">substitutes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></math> into either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">e.g. the negative (opposite) reciprocal of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">the product of the two gradients is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> <strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">so at point M, the curves intersect at right angles&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> <strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">attempts chain rule differentiation on either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent) and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp; <em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">substitutes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></math> into either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> <strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">e.g. the negative reciprocal of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">the product of the two gradients is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">so at point M, the curves intersect at right angles&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15303600","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"At point M, show that the curves y2=4a2-4ax and y2=4b2+4bx intersect at right-angles.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.14—Implicit functions, related rates, optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}